DVDpedia is a DVD cataloging application for Mac OS X developed by Bruji. DVDpedia is shareware and is limited to 25 entries until purchased.
The program searches the Amazon sites (US, UK, Canada, France, Germany and Japan) plus IMDb and several other international sites for information about DVDs, either by entering a keyword or using a scanner or iSight. Users can create smart collections and start a wish list and a borrowed list Entries can be viewed as a standard list, browsed by cover or in the full screen view. The HTML export templates are customizable. DVDpedia comes with Spotlight integration.
